00:50:48.774 --> 00:50:52.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
In our postcard for the month, 
we’ll visit Burundi.

00:50:52.737 --> 00:50:56.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s located
in the often-called “heart of Africa,”

00:50:56.365 --> 00:50:59.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
bordered on the southwest by Lake Tanganyika.

00:51:00.912 --> 00:51:04.123 line:90% position:50% align:center
Burundi is full of green rolling hills,

00:51:04.123 --> 00:51:08.586 line:90% position:50% align:center
cascading waterfalls,
and rich agricultural land.

00:51:09.629 --> 00:51:13.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lake Tanganyika
is the longest freshwater lake in the world

00:51:13.841 --> 00:51:16.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the second deepest.

00:51:16.302 --> 00:51:20.139 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s absolutely bursting with life!

00:51:20.139 --> 00:51:23.017 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over 2,000 species are found here,

00:51:23.017 --> 00:51:26.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
with 500 of them found nowhere else
in the world.

00:51:27.605 --> 00:51:30.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
The local fishermen
tap into this natural bounty,

00:51:30.942 --> 00:51:34.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
hauling in tons of fish every year.

00:51:34.904 --> 00:51:38.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
Burundi is also a preaching paradise
for “fishers of men.”

00:51:39.867 --> 00:51:43.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
There are now over 17,000 publishers
in the country.

00:51:44.288 --> 00:51:49.085 line:90% position:50% align:center
And they had
an incredible Memorial attendance in 2023

00:51:49.085 --> 00:51:52.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
of over 65,000 people.

00:51:53.881 --> 00:51:56.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
But it was not always like this.

00:51:56.300 --> 00:52:01.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
From 1977 to 1993,
the preaching work was banned.

00:52:01.931 --> 00:52:04.308 line:10% position:50% align:center
Our brothers were persecuted

00:52:04.308 --> 00:52:07.478 line:10% position:50% align:center
and even imprisoned for their faith.

00:52:07.478 --> 00:52:10.189 line:10% position:50% align:center
Now when the opportunity comes to preach,

00:52:10.189 --> 00:52:11.857 line:10% position:50% align:center
they seize it.

00:52:12.483 --> 00:52:15.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, Sarah Niyungeko walked

00:52:15.653 --> 00:52:18.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
45 minutes to school each day.

00:52:18.487 --> 00:52:23.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
That way she could save money 
for preaching in seldom-worked territory.

